Package: ppmData
Type: Package
Title: Quasirandom quardature scheme using dirichlet tesselation for spatial Poisson point process models
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(person("Skipton", "Woolley", email = "skipton.woolley@unimelb.edu.au", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Scott", "Foster", email = "scott.foster@csiro.au", role = c("aut")))
Maintainer: Skipton Woolley <skipton.woolley@unimelb.edu.au>
Description: This package generates a set of quasi-random points for a quadrature scheme, we calculate each points weights using a dirichlet tesselation (voronoi) algorithm. The resulting object can be used in existing single and multiple species models in order to extend them to Point Processes.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
